AY, hear me, dearest chum, pray! You shun me like a timid fawn‚ That seeks its mother all the day

By forest brake and upland lawn, 3 Of every passing breeze afraid, And leaf that twitters in the glade.

Let but the wind with sudden rush The whispers of the wood awake, Or lizard green disturb the hush, Quick-darting through the grassy brake, The foolish frightened thing will start, With trembling knees and beating heartff·
